      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Stricter enforcement protects the domestic labor market by preventing the undercutting of wages through an influx of undocumented, low-wage labor. When employers can rely on a pool of undocumented workers willing to accept substandard pay, it drives down wages for all workers in those sectors, including legal citizens. Furthermore, robust border security reduces the strain on public services—like emergency healthcare and social services—that are often overwhelmed by uncontrolled migration. This fiscal stability allows resources to be directed toward legal infrastructure and domestic economic growth.",
      "source": "target",
